I agree this should be an easy puzzle, here's my solution in js :

const words = [...Array(+readline())].map(_ => readline().split(''));
words.forEach(w1 => console.log(w1
    .slice(0, 1 + words.reduce((p, w2) => (w1 !== w2) ? Math.max(p, w1.findIndex((c, i) => c !== w2[i])) : p, 0))
    .join('')));

Which is not optimized at all because I'm testing the whole list for every word, instead of memorizing what has already been tested. But since there's no stress test it works.

