After some time thinking about this, i would imagine a good stress test would be VERY long fake words, with 100's of similar beginning characters. It required this code in order to time out

for i in range(2701,2900): words.append("a"*i)

using that word list (200 words with 2800 characters average) i don't wish that on you to put in it, and i'm not sure i could optimize it much more personally. Some one else maybe could, but having that as the options for testing optimization seems overkill.
